cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with the estimation of the Modulation Transfer Function (MTF) of camera lens systems from photographs, which is a problem in computer vision and image processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses a data-driven supervised learning approach using a convolutional neural network, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of natural images suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
